				\begin{document}$$ \omega- k_{\parallel}v_{\parallel} = \frac{n\varOmega _e}{\gamma} $$\end{document} where ω is the wave frequency, k∥ and v∥ are the parallel components of the wave vector and particle velocity respectively, Ωe is the non-relativistic electron cyclotron frequency, γ is the relativistic factor, and n is a positive or negative integer. When this condition is met, energy can be exchanged between the wave and the particle, leading to acceleration or pitch angle scattering. A more detailed review, including a description of the relevant plasma waves, is given by Millan and Thorne (2007).

